## `app/(tabs)/index.tsx` (Android/Web — 964 lines)
The tab `index` screen for Android/Web. For **clients** it renders the full "Post a Gig" form inline (category, date, time, address, description, duration, gender, payment). For **providers** it shows either a subscription prompt or a list of available gigs with "Accept Gig" buttons. Uses `apiCall` from `@/utils/api`. Has `MessageModal` for success/error feedback. Resets form on success. Does **not** navigate away after posting — stays on the home tab.

Key details:
- `handlePostGig` posts to `/api/gigs` with `clientId`, `category`, `serviceDate`, `serviceTime`, `address`, `description`, `durationDays`, `durationHours`, `paymentOffer`, optional `preferredGender`
- `handleAcceptGig` PUTs to `/api/gigs/${gigId}/accept` with `{ providerId }`
- `fetchAvailableGigs` GETs `/api/gigs/matches/${provider.id}`

---

## `app/(tabs)/index.ios.tsx` (iOS — 932 lines)
Identical logic to `index.tsx` but uses raw `fetch` with `Constants.expoConfig?.extra?.backendUrl` instead of `apiCall`. Wraps client view in `<React.Fragment>` with `<Stack.Screen options={{ title: 'Post a Gig', headerLargeTitle: true }} />`. No `isMountedRef` guard.

