## Key observations for your review:

1. **`post-gig` header is hidden** — `_layout.tsx` sets `headerShown: false` for `post-gig`, so the `Stack.Screen title: 'Post a Gig'` inside `post-gig.tsx` has no effect. There is no back button visible.

2. **Two parallel "Post a Gig" implementations** — `(tabs)/index.tsx` has the full form inline (stays on tab after posting), while `(home)/index.tsx` navigates to `/post-gig` (separate screen). The `(tabs)/index` route and `(home)/index` route coexist — which one renders depends on which tab group is active.

3. **`(home)/index.ios.tsx` renders `gig.title`** but the API likely returns `gig.category`/`gig.description` — this would show blank text for gig cards on iOS in the `(home)` group.

4. **`profile.ios.tsx` is a full copy of `profile.tsx`** — not a re-export, so no circular import risk.

5. **No `SafeAreaProvider`** in `_layout.tsx` — only `GestureHandlerRootView` at root.</span>"
